PROGRAM:
   CB - C program formatter.
USAGE:
    CB <file >file  [-In] [-H]
FUNCTION:
    Used to indent source lines and change { and } to BEGIN and END or
    LOOP and ENDLOOP, etc as needed.

    -In specifies n spaces to indent for each level (default 2).

EXAMPLE:
    CB <file.c |CASE>file.c

